JOHANNESBURG - The North Gauteng High Court will decide whether or not Net1 should be allowed to deduct money from social grant beneficiaries accounts.The parent company of the social grants distributor's challenging a social development department regulation that forbids deductions. The regulations were published in May, prompting the court challenge from Net 1 and its subsidiaries.READ: Grant recipients furious at illegal deductionsThe company wants to continue making deductions and running debit orders from social grants beneficiaries' banks accounts.It also wants the department's regulations to be declared invalid.At the same time, Black Sash is supporting the department, saying it wants the court to protect beneficiaries from exploitative practices.eNCA